@NODE 3. "Author"

      PowerRipper is written by Joakim Ögren in assembler to get the
    program as short and fast as possible. PowerRipper requires at least
    OS2.0 (V37+) to run, since it uses many of 2.0 features to get it
    as fast,short and powerfull as possible. If 3.0 (V39+) is availble
    some of V39 features will be utilized. If you only have 1.3 or
    lower I can only say:   Upgrade 8·}



@ENDNODE

@NODE 4. "Purpose"

      PowerRipper is a utility to find NoiseTracker and ProTracker
    modules in memory and save them to disk. It will search thru all
    memory places availble. It starts with chipmem(s) and continues
    with fastmem(s).



@ENDNODE

@NODE 5. "Installation"

      To run PowerRipper you won't be needing any special libraries. This
    will reduce memory usage. (And maybe not trash your modules)



@ENDNODE

@NODE 6. "Template from CLI"

    ABOUT/S,MULTITASK=SLOW/S

    ABOUT       Show some info about PowerRipper

    MULTITASK   This will cause PowerRipper to multitask a bit.
                You can click in a gadget to stop search.
                You can use the Zoom, everything will be updated
                 during search.
                It will go a little bit slower...

    Please refer to any AmigaDos 2.0 Reference for more information
    about Templates and modifiers.


@ENDNODE

@NODE 7. "All functions"

      Here is the complete documentation for all functions/commands in
    PowerRipper. (In order of appearance). All underlined characters
    are shortcuts that could be used instead of clicking in the gadget.

    Search         This will start the actual search. If you have searched
    Ż             before it will continue where it stopped last time.

    Restart        This will restart the search. It will search from the
    Ż             beginning again.

    Save           This will save the module it has found to disk. You
       Ż          should enter the name in the file gadget.

    About          Show a little text about the program.
    Ż
    Destroy        This will corrupt the module that PR has found (in
          Ż       memory). It will make it unfindable (and unusable).
                  Good if you're ripping many modules and has found
                  a module that you've already ripped.
                   Use this one _very_ carefully!

    Deep Search    This will cause PR to search a little bit better. But
    Ż             there's a chance that it will found things that aren't
                  modules also. This will take a little bit longer.

    File           You should enter the filename here. When you've found
    Ż             a module in memory it will put the modules name in this
                  path. If you have entered a path to the file it will
                  keep the path and just append the filename (the module-
                  name).

    Search Type    You could select here what it will search for:
                  (the moduletype).
                  - M.K.   The original.. ProTracker modules
                  - !PM!   PowerMusic modules! Use optimod.
                  - FLT4   StarTrekker (4-voices)
                  or all types. By just selecting one of the types you'll
                  gain a little bit speed.


    Datafields in the window:

    Memory:       Name of the memory searched. (And address)
    Size:         Calculated size of module in memory.
    Type:         Identifier. (Could be 'M.K.','!PM','FLT4','FLT8'..)
    Pos:          Position in memory
    Name:         Name (if any)
    Len:          Number of positions
    Pat:          Number of patterns
    Status:       Messages are displayed here.

    -------------------------------------------------------------------
    The search can be aborted by pressing left and right mousebutton at
    the same time.
    -------------------------------------------------------------------



@ENDNODE

